## STACK-SPECIFIC RULES
*(Filled from actual project — examples below)*

### Python / FastAPI
- Pydantic schemas for all request/response validation — no raw dicts
- Dependency injection for auth: `current_user: User = Depends(get_current_user)`
- Async all the way — no blocking calls in async routes
- Exception handlers registered globally — no bare `except:` blocks

### React / TypeScript
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any` types
- All forms use react-hook-form with zod validation
- API errors handled centrally — no `.catch()` scattered across components
- No direct DOM manipulation — React state only

### PostgreSQL
- Foreign keys on all relationships — enforce at DB level not just ORM
- Indexes on: all foreign keys, all tenant_id columns, all frequently-queried columns
- Connection pooling configured (pgBouncer or SQLAlchemy pool)

